What is CIM?

CIM (Common information model) is an extensible, object oriented datamodel which contains Information about different parts often of an enterprise it is a Cross-platform standard maintained by DMTF.

Through WMI, developers can use the CIM to create classes that represents various entities such as harddisk drives, applications network routers etc.

CIM has Three levels of classes:

Core: Core classes represents managed objects that apply to all aries of management

Common: Common classes represent managed objects that apply to specific areas of management.

Extended: Extended class represent Managed object that are technology-specific edition to the common classes.



